  "prompt": "How should I start preparing for GSoC 2017?",
  "response": "To prepare for Google Summer of Code (GSoC) 2017, here are some key steps:\n\n1. Choose a Project/Organization\n- Research organizations accepted in previous years\n- Look for organizations aligned with your interests and skills\n- Check their previous GSoC projects\n- Review their project ideas list\n\n2. Technical Preparation\n- Strengthen your programming skills\n- Learn the programming languages used by target organizations\n- Practice coding and contribute to open-source projects\n- Understand version control (Git)\n- Familiarize yourself with GitHub/GitLab\n\n3. Communication\n- Join organization's mailing lists\n- Participate in IRC/Slack channels\n- Engage with community members\n- Ask questions and show genuine interest\n\n4. Develop a Strong Proposal\n- Start early\n- Understand project requirements thoroughly\n- Create a detailed project timeline\n- Demonstrate technical feasibility\n- Show your understanding of the project\n\n5. Build Experience\n- Contribute to open-source projects\n- Submit patches/pull requests\n- Gain visibility in the community\n\n6. Technical Skills\n- Learn relevant frameworks/technologies\n- Study coding standards\n- Practice problem-solving\n\n7. Soft Skills\n- Improve communication\n- Demonstrate reliability\n- Show passion and commitment\n\nRemember, early preparation and active community engagement are key to success.",
